						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged in places. It seems to register an endowment of 15 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold with the interest on which 30 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of ghee was to be supplied to the temple on the day of Tiruvādīrai in Mārgaḻi month. The donor was a native of Irumbēḍu in Pāgaḷūr-nāḍu a division of Śeṅgāṭṭu-kōṭṭam in Toṉḍai nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
